summaries.short: Miranda and Charlotte come to Carrie’s aid, proving what good friends are for. Anthony and Stanford vow to let go of petty arguments.
summaries.full: Miranda rushes to Carrie’s side after a late-night call for help and, later, veers into complicated territory in her attempt to stick up for Nya. Meanwhile, Charlotte tries without success to keep her emotions in check, and Anthony and Stanford vow to let go of petty arguments.

summaries.short: Carrie learns of a surprising development involving Big’s ex. Charlotte worries about how to handle a daughter’s revelation. Miranda ponders the state of her marriage.
summaries.full: Upon learning of a surprising development concerning Big’s ex-wife, Natasha, Carrie goes down a precarious path for answers. Meanwhile, Charlotte worries about how to handle a revelation from her youngest daughter, and Miranda ponders whether her marriage is falling into a roommate situation.

summaries.short: After discussing how to handle change, Carrie is challenged to be “sexually” open on Che’s podcast, Miranda has a disastrous first day of school, and Charlotte tries to impress a fellow mom. And then – another big change no one saw coming.
summaries.full: At a long-awaited brunch, Carrie, Miranda, and Charlotte discuss all the new changes in their lives, including a conspicuous absence from their circle. During a podcast taping, Carrie is thrown off-guard by a personal question from the show’s host, Che Diaz. On her first day of grad school, Miranda commits one faux pas after another in front of her Columbia University law professor, Dr. Nya Wallace, while Charlotte aims to impress Lisa Todd Wexley, a chic and accomplished fellow mom.

summaries.short: Looking to move forward, Carrie meets with self-made real estate broker Seema Patel. Meanwhile, Charlotte plans a high-stakes dinner party for LTW as Miranda and Nya connect over the frank realities of motherhood.
summaries.full: Hoping to move forward, Carrie meets with self-made Manhattan real estate broker Seema Patel, but an offhanded comment threatens to derail their burgeoning friendship. Seizing an opportunity, Charlotte plans a last-minute gathering for LTW - and then quickly grows concerned over the guest list. Later, Miranda and Nya, who is in the throes of IVF, bond over the potential joys – and frank realities – of motherhood.
